<div class="install-preparation-box">
  <h3>Install ADB & Fastboot</h3>
  <br>
  <div name="LinAdb" style="display: block">
    <h4>Debian / Ubuntu</h4>
    <code class="install-code">sudo apt install android-tools-adb android-tools-fastboot</code>
    <br><br>
    <h4>Fedora / OpenSUSE / CentOS</h4>
    <code class="install-code">sudo dnf install android-tools</code>
    <br><br>
    <h4>Arch and derivatives</h4>
    <code class="install-code">sudo pacman -Sy android-tools</code>
    <br><br>
    <h4>Gentoo</h4>
    <code class="install-code">emerge --ask dev-util/android-tools</code>
  </div>
  <div name="WinAdb" style="display: none">
    Install the Google USB driver
    <br><br>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://developer.android.com/studio/run/win-usb" role="button" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" title="Open download source in new tab or window">Get the Google USB Driver ZIP</a>
    <br><br>
    Download this zip file containing ADB & Fastboot from Android SDK
    <br><br>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://release.asteroidos.org/tools/adb_1_0_39+fastboot+ext2simg.zip" role="button">adb-1_0_39+fastboot+ext2simg.zip</a>
    <br><br>
    Extract the content to a folder of your liking.<br>
    Navigate to that folder using the Windows commandline (cmd.exe).
  </div>
  <br><br>
</div>
